{"chapter_summary": "The chapter begins with the Suta Ugraśravas arriving at the Naimiṣa Forest where Śaunaka is performing a twelve-year sacrifice. The sages ask him to recite the Mahābhārata as told by Vyāsa and recited by Vaiśampāyana at Janamejaya's snake sacrifice. The Suta recounts the creation of the universe, the genealogy of gods and kings, and the story of the Pāṇḍavas and Kauravas, including the dice game, exile, and the great war. Dhṛtarāṣṭra laments the destruction, and Sañjaya consoles him with philosophical reflections on time and fate. The chapter ends with praise of the Mahābhārata.", "entities": [{"name": "Ugraśravas (Suta)", "kind": "sage", "aliases": ["Sūta", "Lomaharṣaṇaputra"], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.001", "bhp_01.01.191"]}, {"name": "Śaunaka", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.001"]}, {"name": "Vyāsa", "kind": "sage", "aliases": ["Kṛṣṇa Dvaipāyana", "Parāśarātmaja", "Satyavatīsuta"], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.009", "bhp_01.01.052", "bhp_01.01.053", "bhp_01.01.054", "bhp_01.01.055", "bhp_01.01.056", "bhp_01.01.057", "bhp_01.01.058", "bhp_01.01.059", "bhp_01.01.060", "bhp_01.01.061", "bhp_01.01.062", "bhp_01.01.063", "bhp_01.01.191"]}, {"name": "Vaiśampāyana", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.009", "bhp_01.01.018", "bhp_01.01.057"]}, {"name": "Janamejaya", "kind": "king", "aliases": ["Pārikṣita"], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.008", "bhp_01.01.018", "bhp_01.01.057"]}, {"name": "Dhṛtarāṣṭra", "kind": "king", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.055", "bhp_01.01.065", "bhp_01.01.091", "bhp_01.01.092", "bhp_01.01.095", "bhp_01.01.160"]}, {"name": "Pāṇḍu", "kind": "king", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.055", "bhp_01.01.067", "bhp_01.01.074"]}, {"name": "Vidura", "kind": "king", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.055", "bhp_01.01.094"]}, {"name": "Yudhiṣṭhira", "kind": "king", "aliases": ["Dharmarāja"], "verse_ranges": ["bhp_01.01.066", "bhp_01.01.080", "bhp_01.01.085",